// pesto_uci.c — single-file UCI chess engine using PeSTO evaluation (PST-only).
// Build (macOS): clang -O2 -std=c11 pesto_uci.c -o pesto_uci
// Run: ./pesto_uci
//
// UCI supported: uci, isready, ucinewgame, position, go, stop, quit
// Notes: single-threaded; "stop" is polled during search via select().


/*
    Runs in macOS Terminal (clang-compatible)
    Speaks UCI
    Uses PeSTO (Piece-Square Table Only) tapered evaluation (midgame/endgame PSTs + game phase)
    Implements legal move generation (including castling, en passant, promotions)
    Uses a basic iterative-deepening alpha-beta + quiescence search

    Save as pesto_uci.c, compile, and run as shown after the code.

*/

